<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Virgin Atlantic is set to slash more than 1,000 jobs as it struggles to recover from the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>The British airline, based in Crawley, West Sussex, will reportedly announce the huge cull as early as tomorrow.</p>

<p>It comes just hours after Sir Richard Branson's firm had a £1.2billion rescue package approved by creditors.</p>

<p>The British airline, based in Crawley, West Sussex, will reportedly announce the huge cull as early as tomorrow</p>

<p>And it is less than four months after Virgin Atlantic said it would close its headquarters at Gatwick and axed 3,150 jobs.</p>

<p>The news means the airline's workforce would have nearly halved since before Covid-19 struck, according to Sky News. </p>
